 from ISIS is launched |work=[[Le Monde]] |agency=[[Agence France-Presse]] |date=17 October 2016 |language=fr |access-date=17 October 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017143147/http://www.lemonde.fr/proche-orient/article/2016/10/17/irak-debut-de-l-operation-pour-reprendre-mossoul-des-mains-de-l-ei_5014713_3218.html |archive-date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}\n</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Islamic State leader Baghdadi abandons Mosul fight to field commanders, U.S. and Iraqi sources say |publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=8 March 2017 |first1=Isabel |last1=Coles |first2=John |last2=Walcott |first3=Maher |last3=Chmaytelli |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-baghdadi-idUSKBN16F1DF |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715221546/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-baghdadi-idUSKBN16F1DF |archive-date=15 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/26/world/will-isis-leaders-escape-mosul-bergen/index.html |title=ISIS leaders may flee Mosul as their ranks are decimated |first=Peter |last=Bergen |publisher=CNN |date=27 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026203927/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/26/world/will-isis-leaders-escape-mosul-bergen/index.html |archivedate=26 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=http://aranews.net/2016/06/12000-isis-militants-fighting-mosul/ |title=Over 12,000 ISIS militants fighting for Mosul |date=27 June 2016 |agency=Aranews |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516043248/http://aranews.net/2016/06/12000-isis-militants-fighting-mosul/ |archivedate=16 May 2017 |df=dmy-all |access-date=18 January 2017}}</ref>\n| casualties1 = {{flagicon|Iraq}} 1,200\u20131,400 killed, 6,000\u20137,000+ wounded<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/2-american-soldiers-killed-iraq-u-s-military-says-n792256 |title=2 American Soldiers Killed in Iraq, U.S. Military S