y airstrikes and shelling,<ref>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/sporadic-clashes-in-iraqs-mosul-after-victory-declaration/2017/07/11/3aab681e-6603-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html Clashes shake west Mosul after victory over IS declared] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072901/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/sporadic-clashes-in-iraqs-mosul-after-victory-declaration/2017/07/11/3aab681e-6603-11e7-94ab-5b1f0ff459df_story.html |date=16 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=200ISIS>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/200-isis-fighters-may-remain-in-mosul-us-commander-says|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072759/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2017/07/13/200-isis-fighters-may-remain-in-mosul-us-commander-says.html|url-status=dead|title=200 ISIS fighters may remain in Mosul, US commander says|first=Lucas|last=Tomlinson|date=13 July 2017|archivedate=16 July 2017|website=Fox News}}</ref><ref name=facespockets>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19Z0SR?il=0 |title=Iraq faces pockets of Islamic State resistance in Mosul's Old City |publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=14 July 2017 |accessdate=15 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716072733/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19Z0SR?il=0 |archivedate=16 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> until 20 July.<ref name=\"ISIL remnants\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/remnants-intensify-suicide-attacks-mosuls-old-city/ |title=IS remnants intensify suicide attacks in Mosul's Old City |publisher=Iraqi News |date=20 July 2017 |accessdate=21 July 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170802062113/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/remnants-intensify-suicide-attacks-mosuls-old-city/ |archive-date=2 August 2017 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"250 families\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/250-families-still-besieged-mosuls-old-city-army-officer/ |title=250 families still besieged in Mosul's Old City: Army officer |publisher=Iraqi News |date=20 July 2017 |accessdate=21 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723072303/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/250-families-still-besieged-mosuls-old-city-army-officer/ |archivedate=23 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"residual\"/> The Iraqi military and [[United States Central Command|CENTCOM]] claimed that these were \"clearance operations.\"<ref name=\"daysafter\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19X14G |title=Iraq strikes Islamic State in Mosul days after declaring victory |publisher=Reuters |date=12 July 2017 |accessdate=12 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170712095349/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN19X14G |archivedate=12 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=centiraq>{{Cite web|url=https://www.inherentresolve.mil/Media-Library/News-Releases/Article/1241247/iraqi-security-forces-liberate-mosul/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716170956/http://www.centcom.mil/MEDIA/NEWS-ARTICLES/News-Article-View/Article/1241247/iraqi-security-forces-liberate-mosul/|url-status=dead|title=Iraqi Security Forces liberate Mosul|archivedate=16 July 2017|website=U.S. Central Command}}</ref>\n| campaignbox = {{Campaignbox Iraqi Civil War (2014\u20132017)}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317)''' ({{lang-ar|\u0645\u0639\u0631\u0643\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0635\u0644}}, ''Ma'rakat al-Maw\u1e63il''; {{lang-ckb|\u0634\u06d5\u0695\u06cc \u0645\u0648\u0648\u0633\u06b5}}, ''\u015eeriy M\u00fbsil'') was a major military campaign launched by the Iraqi Government forces with allied militias, the [[Kurdistan Regional Government]], and international forces to retake the city of [[Mosul]] from the [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|Islamic State]] (ISIL),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dunford |first1=Daniel |title=Battle for Mosul: UN prepares for aftermath 'chaos' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37643228 |publisher=BBC News |date=15 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015025231/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37643228 |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The Coming Battle for Mosul |url=https://www.nytimes.com//2016/10/15/opinion/the-coming-battle-for-mosul.html |work=The New York Times |date=14 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015135834/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/15/opinion/the-coming-battle-for-mosul.html |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=von Hein |first1=Matthias |title=Interview: Battle for Mosul likely to lead to power struggle |url=http://www.dw.com/en/interview-battle-for-mosul-likely-to-lead-to-power-struggle/a-36049145 |work=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=14 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015121521/http://www.dw.com/en/interview-battle-for-mosul-likely-to-lead-to-power-struggle/a-36049145 |archivedate=15 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> which had [[fall of Mosul|seized the city]] in June 2014.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Yan |first1=Holly |last2=Muaddi |first2=Nadeem |title=Why the battle for Mosul matters in the fight against ISIS |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/battle-for-mosul/ |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018205707/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/battle-for-mosul/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> During the [[international military intervention against ISIL|military intervention against ISIL]], Iraqi and [[Peshmerga]] forces had already made unsuccessful [[Mosul offensive (2015)|attempts to retake the city in 2015]] and [[Mosul offensive (2016)|again in 2016]], despite limited gains.\n\nThe offensive, dubbed '''Operation \"We Are Coming, Nineveh'''\" ({{lang|ar|\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0645\u0648\u0646 \u064a\u0627 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649}}; ''Qadimun Ya Naynawa''),<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0628\u0627\u062f\u064a \u064a\u0637\u0644\u0642 \u0639\u0644\u0649 \u0639\u0645\u0644\u064a\u0627\u062a \u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 \u062a\u0633\u0645\u064a\u0629 \"\u0642\u0627\u062f\u0645\u0648\u0646 \u064a\u0627 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649\" \u0623\u0645\u0646 |url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/182977/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B9%D9%85%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A/ar |publisher=[[Al Sumaria]] |date=17 October 2016 |language=Arabic |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019170941/http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/182977/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B7%D9%84%D9%82-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%B9%D9%85%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A/ar |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"atlantic1020\">{{cite news |last1=Winter |first1=Charlie |title=How ISIS Is Spinning the Mosul Battle |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2016/10/isis-mosul-propaganda-iraq-kurds-peshmerga/504854/ |work=[[The Atlantic]] |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020230854/http://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2016/10/isis-mosul-propaganda-iraq-kurds-peshmerga/504854/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> began on 16 October 2016, with forces besieging ISIL-controlled areas in the [[Nineveh Governorate]] surrounding Mosul,<ref name=\"ibt1016\">{{cite news |last1=Haddad |first1=Tareq |title='US military has started shelling Mosul' says Peshmerga commander |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/us-military-has-started-shelling-mosul-says-peshmerga-commander-1586650 |work=[[International Business Times]] |date=16 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018173357/http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/us-military-has-started-shelling-mosul-says-peshmerga-commander-1586650 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"bbc1017\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq and Kurdish troops make gains |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37679325 |publisher=BBC News |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132532/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37679325 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"cnn1016\">{{cite news |last1=Blau |first1=Max |last2=Park |first2=Madison |last3=McLaughlin |first3=Eliott C. |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces close in |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/index.html |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017071928/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/index.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and continued with Iraqi troops and Peshmerga fighters engaging ISIL on three fronts outside Mosul, going from village to village in the surrounding area in the largest deployment of Iraqi troops since the [[2003 invasion of Iraq]].<ref name=\"dt1017\">{{cite news |title=What is the battle for Mosul? Everything you need to know about the fight to liberate Isil's last bastion of power in Iraq |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/what-is-the-battle-for-mosul-isils-last-bastion-of-power-in-iraq/ |work=The Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017134739/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/what-is-the-battle-for-mosul-isils-last-bastion-of-power-in-iraq/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The battle was also the world's single largest military operation in nearly 15 years, the largest since the [[2003 invasion of Iraq]].<ref name=\"decade\"/>\n\nAt dawn on 1 November 2016, [[Iraqi Special Operations Forces]] entered the city from the east.<ref name=\"rferl1101\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi Troops Launch Ground Assault On Eastern Neighborhood Of Mosul |url=http://www.rferl.org/a/mosul-iraq-attack-assault-/28087932.html |publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]] |date=1 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161101165042/http://www.rferl.org/a/mosul-iraq-attack-assault-/28087932.html |archivedate=1 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Met with fierce fighting, the government advance into the city was slowed by elaborate defenses and by the presence of civilians,<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces say IS defences, civilians hamper Mosul advance |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-11-06/mosul-iraqi-forces-say-is-defences-and-civilians-hamper-advance/7999152 |publisher=[[ABC News (Australia)]] |date=6 November 2016 |language=en-AU |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106094152/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-11-06/mosul-iraqi-forces-say-is-defences-and-civilians-hamper-advance/7999152 |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> but the [[Prime Minister of Iraq|Iraqi Prime Minister]] [[Haider al-Abadi]] declared \"full liberation of eastern side of Mosul\" on 24 January 2017.<ref name=\"Eastern Mosul liberated\">{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/25/c_136010100.htm |title=Iraqi PM declares full liberation of eastern side of Mosul |publisher=Xinhua |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170131191736/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2017-01/25/c_136010100.htm |archivedate=31 January 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi troops began their offensive to recapture western Mosul on 19 February 2017.<ref name=CNNwestmosul>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/19/middleeast/iraq-starts-operation-to-drive-isis-out-of-west-mosul/index.html |title=Iraq starts operation to drive ISIS out of west Mosul |author1=Faith Karimi |author2=Hamdi Alkhshali |author3=Basma Atassi |publisher=CNN|access-date=2017-02-19 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170219053207/http://www.cnn.com/2017/02/19/middleeast/iraq-starts-operation-to-drive-isis-out-of-west-mosul/index.html |archivedate=19 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2017, the Iraqi Prime Minister arrived in Mosul to announce the victory over ISIL, and an official declaration of victory was proclaimed on 10 July.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/10/iraqi-forces-have-retaken-mosul-u-s-backed-coalition-confirms/465022001/ |title=Iraqi forces have fully retaken Mosul, U.S.-backed coalition confirms |work=USA Today |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711103419/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2017/07/10/iraqi-forces-have-retaken-mosul-u-s-backed-coalition-confirms/465022001/ |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"formally declares victory\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraq PM Abadi formally declares victory |publisher=BBC News |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711051709/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40558836 |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"completely freed\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/07/10/middleeast/mosul-what-next/index.html |title=Mosul completely freed from ISIS: What's next for the city left in ruins? |publisher=Cable News Network |date=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710233845/http://www.cnn.com/2017/07/10/middleeast/mosul-what-next/index.html |archivedate=10 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"clearing\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40555602 |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi troops clearing last IS militants |publisher=BBC News |date=10 July 2017 |accessdate=10 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170710160801/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-40555602 |archivedate=10 July 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, heavy clashes continued in a final pocket of ISIL resistance in the Old City, for almost another 2 weeks.<ref name=\"sporadic\">[http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mosul-isis-victory-airstrike-1.4198966 Sporadic clashes continue in Mosul after victory declared] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711111135/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/mosul-isis-victory-airstrike-1.4198966 |date=11 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"250 families\" /><ref name=\"residual\" /><ref name=\"July 22 airstrike log\">{{cite web|url=http://www.inherentresolve.mil/Portals/14/Documents/Strike%20Releases/2017/07July/20170722%20Strike%20Release.pdf?ver=2017-07-22-060600-830|title=Strike Release: July 22, 2017|publisher=[[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF\u2013OIR]]|date=22 July 2017|access-date=29 November 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140142/http://www.inherentresolve.mil/Portals/14/Documents/Strike%20Releases/2017/07July/20170722%20Strike%20Release.pdf?ver=2017-07-22-060600-830|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was estimated that removing the explosives from Mosul and repairing the city over the next 5 years would require $50 billion (2017 USD),<ref name=\"numbers\">{{cite web |url=https://www.stripes.com/news/middle-east/by-the-numbers-the-fight-against-islamic-state-in-iraq-1.477461 |title=By the numbers: The fight against Islamic State in Iraq |publisher=Stars and Stripes |date=11 July 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711084915/https://www.stripes.com/news/middle-east/by-the-numbers-the-fight-against-islamic-state-in-iraq-1.477461 |archivedate=11 July 2017 |df=dmy-all |access-date=12 July 2017}}</ref> while Mosul's Old City alone would cost about US$1 billion to repair.<ref name=\"completely freed\" />\n\nThe Battle of Mosul was concurrent with the [[Battle of Sirte (2016)|Battle of Sirte]] in Libya and the [[Raqqa campaign (2016\u201317)|Raqqa campaign]] conducted by the [[Syrian Democratic Forces]] (SDF) against [[Raqqa|ISIL's capital city]] and stronghold in [[Syria]].<ref>{{cite news |title=This is why everything you've read about the wars in Syria and Iraq could be wrong |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/syria-aleppo-iraq-mosul-isis-middle-east-conflict-assad-war-everything-youve-read-could-be-wrong-a7451656.html |date=2 December 2016 |work=The Independent |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202123936/http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/syria-aleppo-iraq-mosul-isis-middle-east-conflict-assad-war-everything-youve-read-could-be-wrong-a7451656.html |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n{{TOC limit|4}}\n\n== Background ==\n[[File:2016.08 Mosul area.svg|{{largethumb}}|Map of the territorial control during the 2016 Mosul offensive, as of August 2016]]\n=== General background ===\n{{Main|Fall of Mosul|Mosul offensive (2015)}}\nMosul is Iraq's second most populous city. It [[fall of Mosul|fell]] to 800\u20131,500 ISIL militants in June 2014, because of the largely [[Sunni Islam|Sunni]] population's deep distrust of the primarily [[Shia]] Iraqi government, and its corrupt armed forces.<ref name=\"lemonde1017\" /><ref name=\"reuters1016\">{{cite news |title=Factbox: Once-tolerant Mosul site of Iraq push against Islamic State |url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/factbox-once-tolerant-mosul-iraq-push-against-islamic-232623181.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=16 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019012341/https://www.yahoo.com/news/factbox-once-tolerant-mosul-iraq-push-against-islamic-232623181.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was in the [[Great Mosque of al-Nuri (Mosul)|Great Mosque in Mosul]] that ISIL leader [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]] declared the beginning of ISIL's self-proclaimed \"caliphate\" which spans Iraq and Syria.<ref name=\"reuters1016\" /> The original population of 2.5 million has fallen to approximately 1.5 million after two years of ISIL rule. The city was once extremely diverse, with ethnic minorities including [[Armenians in Iraq|Armenians]], [[Yazidis]], [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]], [[Iraqi Turkmen|Turkmen]], and [[Shabak people|Shabak]] people, all of whom have suffered and continue to suffer considerably under the (majority Sunni Arab) Islamic State.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bulos |first1=Nabih |title=The battle in Iraq that could turn the tide against Islamic State: The fight for Mosul is about to begin |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161002-snap-story.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=2 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017163757/http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161002-snap-story.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Mosul remains the last stronghold of ISIL in Iraq,<ref name=\"nyt1017\">{{cite news |last1=Gordon |first1=Michael R. |last2=Arango |first2=Tim |title=Kurdish Troops Advance on ISIS-Held Villages East of Mosul |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul-battle.html |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The New York Times |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017120726/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/iraq-isis-mosul-battle.html |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> and the anticipated offensive to reclaim it was promoted as the \"mother of all battles.\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ensor |first1=Josie |title=Isil 'launches suicide attacks' on Kurdish forces in Mosul as bloody battle to retake terror group's Iraq stronghold begins |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132203/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi army begins 'mother of all battles' to reclaim Mosul |url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/world/iraqi-army-begins-mother-of-all-battles-to-reclaim-mosul/ar-AAj2lYY?li=BBoPWjQ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |publisher=msn.com |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018212622/http://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/world/iraqi-army-begins-mother-of-all-battles-to-reclaim-mosul/ar-AAj2lYY?li=BBoPWjQ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Chris |title=ISIS under devastating attack as 'mother of all battles' begins in Mosul |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/isis-under-devastating-attack-mother-9064344 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Mirror |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019082003/http://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/isis-under-devastating-attack-mother-9064344 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Wedeman |first1=Ben |title=Will ISIS be pushed easily from Mosul? |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/11/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-conflict-explainer/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=25 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018213104/http://www.cnn.com/2016/07/11/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-conflict-explainer/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Preparations for the battle ===\n{{Main|Mosul offensive (2016)}}\nIn the weeks leading up to the ground offensive, the US-led [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|CJTF \u2013 OIR]] coalition bombed ISIL targets, and the Iraqi Army made gradual advances on the city.<ref name=\"dt1017\" /> [[Royal Air Force]]'s [[General Atomics MQ-9 Reaper|Reaper]] drones, [[Eurofighter Typhoon|Typhoons]], and [[Panavia Tornado|Tornados]] targeted \"[[rocket launchers]], [[ammunition]] [[Stockpile (military)|stockpiles]], [[artillery]] pieces and [[Mortar (weapon)|mortar]] positions\" in the 72 hours before the ground assault began.<ref>{{cite news |title=Isil 'launches suicide attacks' on Kurdish forces in Mosul as bloody battle to retake terror group's Iraq stronghold begins |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017132203/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/10/17/bloody-battle-to-retake-mosul-begins-as-iraqi-forces-move-to-wip2/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Airborne leaflet propaganda|Leaflets]] dropped on the city by the Iraqi military advised young male residents to \"rise up\" against ISIL when the battle began.<ref name=\"nyt1017\" /> To prepare defenses against the assault, ISIL operatives dug 4&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup> holes around the city, which they planned to fill with burning oil to reduce visibility<ref name=\"dt1017\" /> and slow advances.<ref name=\"ptv\">{{cite web |url=http://www.presstv.com/Detail/2016/10/17/489433/Iraq-Mosul-five-villages |title=PressTV-LIVE UPDATE: Final push to retake Mosul |work=presstv.com |accessdate=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017144408/http://presstv.com/Detail/2016/10/17/489433/Iraq-Mosul-five-villages |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> They also built hundreds of elaborate tunnels in the villages surrounding Mosul, rigged with explosives and booby-traps, and laid [[improvised explosive device]]s (IEDs) and mines along the roads.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |title=Abandoned villages on road to Mosul rigged with tunnels and bombs |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12J1OX |accessdate=3 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=20 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104010848/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKCN12J1OX |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> There was considerable concern that ISIL might employ chemical weapons against soldiers and civilians.<ref name=\"aj1030\">{{cite news |last1=de Bretton-Gordon |first1=Hamish |title=Chemical dangers in the battle for Mosul |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2016/10/chemical-dangers-battle-mosul-161026091359992.html |accessdate=3 November 2016 |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=30 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102105412/http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2016/10/chemical-dangers-battle-mosul-161026091359992.html |archivedate=2 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Iraqi sources, the assault towards Mosul was being waged from Al-Khazer axis (east of Mosul), [[Mosul Dam]] (northern axis), [[Bashiqa|Baashiqa]] axis (eastern axis), Al-Qayyarah axis (southern axis), and Talul el-Baj- Al-Khadr axis (southwestern axis).<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://jcpa.org/battle-mosul-aftermath/ |title=The Battle for Mosul and Its Aftermath |date=2016-10-26 |newspaper=Jerusalem Center For Public Affairs |language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-13 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114002054/http://jcpa.org/battle-mosul-aftermath/ |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Forces involved in the offensive ===\n[[File:Lt. Gen. Stephen J. Townsend Qayyarah September 2016.jpg|thumb|U.S. Lt. Gen. [[Stephen J. Townsend]], commander of the Combined Joint Task Force, at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]], 22 September 2016]]\nAbout 3,000\u20135,000 ISIL fighters were estimated to be in Mosul city, according to the United States Department of Defense.<ref name=\"AV\">{{cite AV media |people=Peter Cook, various reporters |date=17 October 2016 |title=Defense Department Briefing |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?417070-1/peter-cook-briefs-reporters-military-operations-mosul | access-date = 17 October 2016 |time=23:02 |location=Arlington, Virginia, United States |publisher=[[C-SPAN]] |quote=The estimate [of ISL fighters in Mosul] I've seen was\u2026 3,000 to 5,000\u2026 We've seen other numbers that are higher. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018045203/https://www.c-span.org/video/?417070-1%2Fpeter-cook-briefs-reporters-military-operations-mosul |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Other estimates ranged as low as 2,000 and high as 12,000 ISIL fighters.<ref name=\"lemonde1017\" /><ref name=\"auto2\" /> ''[[Mosul Eye]]'' estimated approximately 8,000\u20139,000 fighters loyal to ISIL, with \"half of them... highly trained, and the rest... either teenagers or not well trained. About ten percent of the fighters are foreign (Arabs and non-Arabs). The rest are Iraqis. Most are from Nineveh's townships and districts.\"<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Robin |date=27 October 2016 |title=The Secret Eye Inside Mosul |url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-secret-eye-inside-mosul |newspaper=The New Yorker |access-date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028135139/http://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-secret-eye-inside-mosul |archivedate=28 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Prior to the start of the battle, in late September 2016, it was estimated that around 20,000 ISIL fighters were living in Mosul,<ref name=\"push deeper\">{{cite web |url=http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/ |title=Forces push deeper into key IS-held northern town |publisher=Samachar Today |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170227155947/http://samachartoday.com/2016/09/27/forces-push-deeper-into-key-is-held-northern-town/ |archivedate=27 February 2017 |df=dmy-all |access-date=26 February 2017}}</ref> many of whom later fled the city to Syria and Ar-Raqqah, when Iraqi forces began to besiege Mosul.\n\nThe Iraqi-led coalition was initially estimated by [[CNN]] to have 94,000 members,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/ |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces inflict 'heavy losses' on ISIS |last1=Walsh |first1=Nick |last2=Blau |first2=Max |last3=Grinberg |first3=Emanuella |last4=Hume |first4=Tim |date=17 October 2016 |website=CNN |access-date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017194025/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-begins-iraq/ |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> but this number was later revised upward to 108,500;<ref name=\"Mosul battle forces\">{{cite news |last=Hume |first=Tim |date=25 October 2016 |title=Battle for Mosul: How ISIS is fighting to keep its Iraqi stronghold |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/ |newspaper=CNN |access-date=29 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161029044039/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/24/middleeast/iraq-mosul-isis-tactics/ |archivedate=29 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> 54,000 to 60,000 [[Iraqi security forces]] (ISF) soldiers, 16,000 [[Popular Mobilization Forces]] (PMF) fighters (also referred to as PMU), and 40,000 [[Peshmerga]] (including approximately 200 Iranian Kurdish female fighters from the [[Kurdistan Freedom Party]] (PAK))<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dehghanpisheh |first1=Babak |last2=Georgy |first2=Michael |title=Kurdish women fighters battle Islamic State with machineguns and songs |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-womenfighters-idUSKBN12Y2DC |accessdate=5 November 2016 |agency=Reuters |date=4 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161104163756/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-mosul-womenfighters-idUSKBN12Y2DC |archivedate=4 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> were deployed in the battle.<ref name=\"cnn1017\" /><ref name=\"ptv\" /> The Iraqi and Peshmerga forces deployed for the Mosul operation were estimated to have outnumbered the ISIL militants present by 10-to-1.<ref name=\"decade\"/>\n\nAmong the PMF units, the [[Nineveh Plain Protection Units]] composed of [[Assyrian people|Assyrians]] are among the paramilitary forces in the government coalition.<ref name=\"NPF\">{{cite news |url=http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |title=NPF declaring their participation to Mosul offensive |publisher=Syriac International News Agency |date=18 October 2016 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018133332/http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Lodge |first1=Carey |title=Christian Forces Will 'Fight Relentlessly' To Free Mosul From ISIS |url=http://www.christiantoday.com/article/christian.forces.will.fight.relentlessly.to.free.mosul.from.isis/98274.htm |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Christian Today |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20171010054612/https://www.christiantoday.com/article/christian.forces.will.fight.relentlessly.to.free.mosul.from.isis/98274.htm |archivedate=10 October 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Shia militias, including several brigades of the paramilitary organization Hashd al-Shaabi, the [[Peace Companies]], [[Kata'ib Hezbollah]], the [[League of the Righteous]], the [[Badr Organization]], Saraya Ashura, Saraya Khorasani, [[Kata'ib al-Imam Ali]], [[Harakat Hezbollah al-Nujaba]] and [[Turkmen Brigades (PMU)|Turkmen Brigades]] also took part.<ref name=\"PMF cut off\">{{cite web |url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/iraqi-popular-mobilization-forces-attempt-to-cut-off-islamic-state-in-mosul.php |title=Iraqi PMF attempts to cut off Islamic State in Mosul |publisher=The Long War Journal |author1=Amir Toumaj |date=4 November 2016 |accessdate=5 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105133800/http://www.longwarjournal.org/archives/2016/11/iraqi-popular-mobilization-forces-attempt-to-cut-off-islamic-state-in-mosul.php |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"lobs1017\" /> The [[Ezidi]] community of the Sinjar region contributed the [[Sinjar Resistance Units]] (YB\u015e) and [[\u00caz\u00eedxan Women's Units]] (YJ\u00ca),<ref name=Ezidi>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/isis-iraq-kurdish-trained-yazidi-women-launch-operation-revenge-free-women-a7416906.html |title=All-female Yazidi militia launches operation for revenge on Isis in northern Iraq |publisher=The Independent |date=14 November 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114170145/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/isis-iraq-kurdish-trained-yazidi-women-launch-operation-revenge-free-women-a7416906.html |archivedate=14 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> which are operating in concert with Sunni Arab [[Shammar]] tribal militias and [[People's Defence Forces]] (HPG) of the [[Kurdistan Workers' Party]] (PKK).<ref>{{cite news |title=On patrol with the Sinjar Resistance Units |url=https://widerimage.reuters.com/story/on-patrol-with-the-sinjar-resistance-units |accessdate=1 December 2016 |agency=Reuters |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202035410/https://widerimage.reuters.com/story/on-patrol-with-the-sinjar-resistance-units |archivedate=2 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Other [[Assyrian people|Assyrian]] forces involved in the planned offensive included the [[Nineveh Plain Forces]] (NPF) and [[Dwekh Nawsha]], who are allied to the Peshmerga.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |title=NPF declaring their participation to Mosul offensive \u2013 Syriac International News Agency |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018133332/http://www.syriacsnews.com/npf-declaring-participation-mosul-offensive/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all |access-date=18 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMcLRJT7CAA |title=Dwekh Nawsha Document the what happened in Batnaya.P9 |date=16 January 2017 |via=YouTube |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170203075731/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yMcLRJT7CAA |archivedate=3 February 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Peshmerga soldiers prepare to conduct a combined arms live-fire exercise near Erbil, Iraq.jpg|left|thumb|[[Peshmerga]] soldiers prepare to conduct a combined arms live-fire exercise with an Italian instructor near [[Erbil]], on 12 October 2016.]]\nAn [[Combined Joint Task Force \u2013 Operation Inherent Resolve|international coalition]] of 60 nations, led by the United States, is supporting Iraq's war against ISIL, providing logistical and air support, intelligence, and advice.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraq, Syria Make Significant Strides Countering ISIL, Press Secretary |url=http://www.defense.gov/News/Article/Article/976204/iraq-syria-make-significant-strides-countering-isil-press-secretary-says |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018233950/http://www.defense.gov/News/Article/Article/976204/iraq-syria-make-significant-strides-countering-isil-press-secretary-says |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The international coalition forces are headquartered {{convert|60|km}} south of Mosul at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]] (or Q-West) in [[Qayyarah]], which was retaken from ISIL in June.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Forey |first1=Samuel |title=Bataille de Mossoul: reportage \u00e0 Qayyarah, dans le QG de la coalition |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/16/01003-20161016ARTFIG00175-qayyarah-dernier-verrou-strategique-avant-mossoul.php |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=16 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017124143/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/16/01003-20161016ARTFIG00175-qayyarah-dernier-verrou-strategique-avant-mossoul.php |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> About 560 U.S. troops from the [[101st Airborne Division]] were deployed to Q-West for the battle, including command and control elements, a security detachment, an airfield operations team, and logistics and communications specialists.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sisk |first1=Richard |title=101st Soldiers Deploying to Bolster Fight Against ISIS in Iraq |url=http://www.military.com/daily-news/2016/08/08/101st-soldiers-deploying-to-bolster-fight-against-isis-in-iraq.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Military.com |date=8 August 2016 |language=en |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019001248/http://www.military.com/daily-news/2016/08/08/101st-soldiers-deploying-to-bolster-fight-against-isis-in-iraq.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The U.S. deployed [[HIMARS]] rocket launchers and [[M777 howitzer]]s, manned by the 101st's 2nd Brigade Combat Team and the Golf Company, 526th Brigade Support Battalion. The French army deployed four [[CAESAR self-propelled howitzer|CAESAR]] howitzers and 150 to 200 soldiers at Qayyarah, with 600 more French troops announced at the end of September.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chapleau |first1=Philippe |title=Les quatre Caesar de Qayyarah ont d\u00e9j\u00e0 donn\u00e9 de la voix |url=http://lignesdedefense.blogs.ouest-france.fr/archive/2016/09/29/les-caesar-de-qayyarak-ont-tonne-les-20-27-et-29-septembre-16885.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Ouest-France |date=29 September 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018210759/http://lignesdedefense.blogs.ouest-france.fr/archive/2016/09/29/les-caesar-de-qayyarak-ont-tonne-les-20-27-et-29-septembre-16885.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> An additional 150 French soldiers are in [[Erbil]], east of Mosul, training Peshmerga.<ref name=\"lobs1017\">{{cite news |title=Bataille de Mossoul : qui participe \u00e0 la reconqu\u00eate ? |url=http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/monde/20161017.OBS9927/bataille-de-mossoul-qui-participe-a-la-reconquete.html |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=L'Observer |date=17 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018231500/http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/monde/20161017.OBS9927/bataille-de-mossoul-qui-participe-a-la-reconquete.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The aircraft carrier ''[[French aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle|Charles de Gaulle]]'', with a squadron of 24 [[Dassault Rafale|Rafale M jets]], was deployed from [[Toulon]] to the Syrian coast to support the operation against ISIL through airstrikes and reconnaissance missions; 12 other Rafale jets are operating out of [[French Air Force]] bases in Jordan and the [[United Arab Emirates]] (UAE).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Licourt |first1=Julien |title=Premi\u00e8res op\u00e9rations depuis le Charles-de-Gaulle avant l'offensive sur Mossoul |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/09/30/01003-20160930ARTFIG00055-irak-la-coalition-debute-son-offensive-sur-mossoul.php |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=30 September 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020035332/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/09/30/01003-20160930ARTFIG00055-irak-la-coalition-debute-son-offensive-sur-mossoul.php |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"cnncdg\">{{cite news |last1=Pleitgen |first1=Fred |title=On board the French nuclear carrier battling ISIS |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/france-nuclear-carrier-mosul-iraq-isis/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019044158/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/17/middleeast/france-nuclear-carrier-mosul-iraq-isis/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> 80 [[Special Operations Command (Australia)|Australian special forces]] soldiers and 210 [[Canadian Special Operations Forces Command]] (CANSOFCOM) soldiers were also deployed to assist the Peshmerga. In addition, the [[Canadian Forces]] [[21 Electronic Warfare Regiment]] was also reported to be in the area, working to intercept and relay ISIL communications, while a Role 2 [[Canadian Forces Health Services Group|Canadian Army field hospital]] with 60 personnel has been set up to treat Peshmerga casualties.<ref name=\"Okra\">{{cite web |last1=Greene |first1=Andrew |title=Islamic State: Australia's special forces to assist Iraq military in battle for Mosul |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-10-17/australian-special-forces-to-assist-military-operation-to-retak/7939556 |website=ABC News |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017131032/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-10-17/australian-special-forces-to-assist-military-operation-to-retak/7939556 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"CANSOFCOM\">{{cite web |last1=Chase |first1=Steven |title=Canadian forces providing crucial support in battle to recapture Mosul |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadian-forces-providing-crucial-support-in-battle-to-recapture-mosul/article32403507/ |website=The Globe and Mail |accessdate=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018235608/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/canadian-forces-providing-crucial-support-in-battle-to-recapture-mosul/article32403507/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n[[File:An Iraqi soldier attending a course on chemical, biological, radiological and nuclear defense training at Camp Taji.jpg|thumb|An Iraqi soldier during a course on chemical, biological, radiological and nuclear defense training at [[Camp Taji]]. Coalition forces expressed fears ISIL may use chemical weapons during the Battle of Mosul.]]\nThe [[Arab Socialist Ba'ath Party \u2013 Iraq Region|Ba'ath loyalists]] group, known to be led by [[Saddam Hussein]]'s former vice president [[Izzat Ibrahim al-Douri]], issued a statement before the start of operations calling for the people of the city to start an uprising against ISIL and announced that they will fight the \"terrorist organization.\"<ref name=\"Naqshabandi \u2013 Bawwabat Al-Arab\">{{cite web |title=\u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0648\u0635\u0644.. \u062c\u064a\u0634 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0642\u0634\u0628\u0646\u062f\u064a\u0629 \u064a\u0646\u0641\u064a \u0627\u0634\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0643 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0634\u0645\u0631\u0643\u0629 \u0645\u0639 \"\u062f\u0627\u0639\u0634\" |url=https://www.albawabhnews.com/2168253 |website=Bawwabat Al-Arab |accessdate=20 October 2016 |language=Arabic |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021013000/http://www.albawabhnews.com/2168253 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Naqshabandi \u2013 Azzaman\">{{cite web |title=\u0627\u0644\u0647\u062c\u0648\u0645 \u064a\u0646\u062c\u0632 \u0623\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0641\u0647 \u0641\u064a \u0633\u0647\u0644 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 |url=http://www.azzaman.com/?p=180750 |website=Azzaman |accessdate=20 October 2016 |language=Arabic |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018180406/http://www.azzaman.com/?p=180750 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== The battle ==\n{{Main|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase One|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase Two|Timeline of the Battle of Mosul (2016\u201317): Phase Three}}\n=== October: Phase One and initial advances ===\n[[File:M109A6 Paladin at Qayyarah October 2016.jpg|thumb|upright=1.3636364|A U.S. Army [[M109A6 Paladin]] conducts a fire mission at [[Qayyarah Airfield West]], in support of the Iraqi security forces' push toward Mosul, 17 October 2016.]]\nOn 16 October 2016, Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi declared the beginning of the assault to recapture the city of Mosul.<ref name=\"cnn1016\"/> Officials reported howitzers firing on ISIL targets later that day.<ref name=\"ibt1016\"/> The main assault began on 17 October at approximately 6{{nbsp}}a.m., local time,<ref name=\"nyt1017\"/> with shelling and the arrival of armored vehicles to the front lines.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/in-isis-held-mosul-beheadings-and-hints-of-resistance-as-battle-nears.html Iraqi Forces Attack Mosul, Seeking to Dislodge Islamic State {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170125101753/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/17/world/middleeast/in-isis-held-mosul-beheadings-and-hints-of-resistance-as-battle-nears.html |date=25 January 2017}} ''The New York Times'' (16 October 2016)</ref> The Peshmerga in the Khazir region, east of Mosul, started the ground assault by advancing on ISIL-held villages from three fronts, while Iraqi security forces advanced from the south.<ref>[http://www.deccanchronicle.com/world/middle-east/171016/iraqs-kurdish-forces-launch-fresh-push-east-of-mosul.html Iraq's Kurdish forces launch fresh push east of Mosul] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018001849/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/world/middle-east/171016/iraqs-kurdish-forces-launch-fresh-push-east-of-mosul.html |date=18 October 2016}} ''Deccan Chronicle'' (17 October 2016)</ref> Iraqi troops advanced on the [[Bartella]] area east of Mosul while ISIL fighters fired mortars at Peshmerga.<ref name=\"wsj1017\">{{cite news |last1=El-Ghobashy |first1=Tamer |last2=Nabhan |first2=Ali A. |last3=Kesling |title=Iraq Forces Begin Battle to Dislodge ISIS From Mosul |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/islamic-state-braces-as-iraq-prepares-mosul-offensive-1476642193 |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=[[The Wall Street Journal]] |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161017003332/http://www.wsj.com/articles/islamic-state-braces-as-iraq-prepares-mosul-offensive-1476642193 |archivedate=17 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The President of KRG, [[Massoud Barzani]], said that Peshmerga and Iraqi government fighters retook 200 square kilometers (80 square miles) from ISIL on the first day of fighting.<ref name=\"aj1017\">{{cite news |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces claim gains against ISIL |url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-iraqi-forces-claim-gains-isil-161017125543255.html |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Al Jazeera |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018001559/http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/10/battle-mosul-iraqi-forces-claim-gains-isil-161017125543255.html |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi government officials reported inflicting severe casualties and destruction of equipment on ISIL forces in the Hamdaniya district southeast of Mosul. Wounded ISIL fighters reported to have been transferred to their de facto capital [[Raqqa]], in Syria, for medical aid.<ref name=\"cnn1017\"/> Some ISIL fighters were reported shaving their beards and getting rid of their Afghan uniforms.<ref>{{cite news |title=ISIS families flee Mosul amid intense aerial bombing |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/isis-families-flee-mosul-amid-intense-aerial-bombing/ |accessdate=17 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018071546/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/isis-families-flee-mosul-amid-intense-aerial-bombing/ |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Mosul's \"Freedom Bridge\" was destroyed in the fighting.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hennessy-Fiske |first1=Molly |title=A 'decisive battle': Determination energizes Iraqi forces in fight to retake Mosul from Islamic State |url=https://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161017-snap-story.html |accessdate=4 November 2016 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105160849/http://www.latimes.com/world/middleeast/la-fg-iraq-mosul-20161017-snap-story.html |archivedate=5 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Battle of Mosul - Iraqi security forces transport combat equipment 2.jpg|thumb|Iraqi security forces transport two [[BMP-1]] infantry fighting vehicles to tactical assembly areas with assistance from the 313th Movement Control Battalion forward element, on 18 October 2016, near [[Makhmur, Iraq]]]]\nOn 18 October, the Iraqi government declared to have captured 20 villages from ISIL within 24 hours of fighting.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chmaytelli |first=Maher |date=18 October 2016 |title=Iraqi forces announce progress in Mosul offensive |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN12I0A6 |newspaper=Reuters |location=Baghdad |access-date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018065946/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-mideast-crisis-iraq-mosul-idUSKBN12I0A6 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> On the southern front, Iraqi troops retook several villages near [[Qayyarah]], including al-Sirt, Bajwaniya, al-Hud and al-Mashraf, and parts of the al-Hamdaniya District southeast of Mosul,<ref name=\"liberate new villages\" /> as well as the al-Shura District.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces liberate al-Shura district south of Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-liberate-al-shura-district-south-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019152529/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/iraqi-forces-liberate-al-shura-district-south-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> [[Iraqi Federal Police]] also regained control of 56 oilfields in the Qayyarah district.<ref name=\"liberate new villages\">{{cite news |last1=Goran |first1=Baxtiyar |title=Iraqi army liberate new villages in second day of Mosul operation |url=http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/620fd9a5-43c2-437f-98b8-5b234e130eee/iraqi-army-liberate-new-villages-in-second-day-of-mosul-operation- |accessdate=20 October 2016 |publisher=Kurdistan 24 |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021004103/http://www.kurdistan24.net/en/news/620fd9a5-43c2-437f-98b8-5b234e130eee/iraqi-army-liberate-new-villages-in-second-day-of-mosul-operation- |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> According to reports, the Peshmerga met little resistance on the eastern front, while Iraqi and PMF fighters coming from the south faced tougher resistance from ISIL.<ref name=\"guardian1018\">{{cite news |last1=Chulov |first1=Martin |last2=Hawramy |first2=Fazel |last3=Borger |first3=Julian |last4=Wintour |first4=Patrick |title=Battle for Mosul: Iraqi forces converge in decisive battle against Isis |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/kurds-lead-advance-on-mosul-in-decisive-battle-for-iraqs-second-city |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018000353/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/oct/17/kurds-lead-advance-on-mosul-in-decisive-battle-for-iraqs-second-city |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Iraqi Army forces stormed Qaraqosh ([[Bakhdida]]), once the largest Assyrian town in Iraq, and fought with ISIL fighters who remained holed up, while also nearing Hammam al-'Alil.<ref name=\"straightstimes\">{{cite news |title=Iraqi forces make gains in bid to retake ISIS-held Mosul, France to host international talks |url=http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-ahead-of-schedule-in-operation-to-retake-mosul-from-isis-pentagon |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=The Straits Times |agency=AFP/Reuters |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019050753/http://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/iraqi-forces-ahead-of-schedule-in-operation-to-retake-mosul-from-isis-pentagon |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mareschal |first1=Edouard de |title=L'arm\u00e9e irakienne reprend le contr\u00f4le partiel de Qaraqosh la chr\u00e9tienne |url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/18/01003-20161018ARTFIG00331-l-armee-irakienne-reprend-le-controle-partiel-de-qaraqosh-la-chretienne.php |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Le Figaro |date=18 October 2016 |language=fr-FR |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019142956/http://www.lefigaro.fr/international/2016/10/18/01003-20161018ARTFIG00331-l-armee-irakienne-reprend-le-controle-partiel-de-qaraqosh-la-chretienne.php |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"rudaw1018\">{{cite news |title=LIVE UPDATES MOSUL BATTLE: Day 2 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/18102016 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=[[Rudaw Media Network]] |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021233134/http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/18102016 |archivedate=21 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Displaced Christians celebrate as Iraq's military forces enter town near Mosul |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/displaced-christians-celebrate-as-iraqs-military-forces-enter-town-near-mosul-3090837/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=The Indian Express |agency=AFP |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019214634/http://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/displaced-christians-celebrate-as-iraqs-military-forces-enter-town-near-mosul-3090837/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Iraqi and Peshmerga advance had been slowed down during the same day due to suicide bombers, roadside [[Improvised explosive devices|IEDs]] and oil fires, and the allied forces were carrying out street-by-street search operations to clear out ISIL forces from the outskirts of Mosul city.<ref>{{cite news |title=Suicide bomber slams into Iraqi troops advancing on Mosul |url=http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/10/18/07/29/suicide-bomber-slams-into-iraqi-column |accessdate=18 October 2016 |agency=9News.com.au |date=17 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019013714/http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/10/18/07/29/suicide-bomber-slams-into-iraqi-column |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kurds planning fresh push to recapture Mosul |url=https://news.sky.com/story/kurds-planning-fresh-push-to-recapture-mosul-10621939 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Sky News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018222641/https://news.sky.com/story/kurds-planning-fresh-push-to-recapture-mosul-10621939 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Peshmerga later paused their advance while the Iraqi Army continued its advance.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kurds pause in Mosul offensive, say Iraqi Army will advance |url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/international/kurds-pause-in-mosul-offensive-say-iraqi-army-will-advance/article9234288.ece |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=The Hindu |date=18 October 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt this point in time, the Coalition strategy was reported to be to encircle Mosul completely, after which Iraqi troops would advance into the city center.<ref name=\"bbcnews1018\">{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: EU 'should expect influx of jihadists' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37689210 |accessdate=18 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018135845/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37689210 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> As the Iraqi Army advanced on Mosul, rebellion against ISIL broke out in the city, though ISIL forces put down the revolts within a couple of days.<ref>{{cite news |title=Baghdadi survives coup attempt by ISIS Islamic Police in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/baghdadi-survives-coup-attempt-isis-islamic-police-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019020800/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/baghdadi-survives-coup-attempt-isis-islamic-police-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Rebellious youths storm ISIS headquarters in Mosul, raise Iraqi flag |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/rebellious-youths-storm-isis-headquarters-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019152328/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/rebellious-youths-storm-isis-headquarters-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Armed uprising against ISIS begins in Mosul |url=http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/armed-uprising-isis-begins-mosul/ |accessdate=18 October 2016 |work=Iraqi News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019145804/http://www.iraqinews.com/iraq-war/armed-uprising-isis-begins-mosul/ |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe Iraqi Army resumed fighting on 19 October, surrounding Qaraqosh, while ISIL deployed snipers and car bombs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mosul battle: Iraqi army 'besieges' Christian town of Qaraqosh |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37691830 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=BBC News |date=18 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018235507/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-37691830 |archivedate=18 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Les forces irakiennes s'appr\u00eatent \u00e0 reprendre une ville chr\u00e9tienne proche de Mossoul (Iraqi forces ready to retake Christian village near Mosul) |url=http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1013499/les-forces-irakiennes-sappretent-a-reprendre-une-ville-chretienne-proche-de-mossoul.html |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=L'Orient-Le Jour |agency=AFP |date=19 October 2016 |language=fr |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019213046/http://www.lorientlejour.com/article/1013499/les-forces-irakiennes-sappretent-a-reprendre-une-ville-chretienne-proche-de-mossoul.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Lt. Gen. Qassim al-Maliki declared that Iraqi forces had captured 13 villages north and northeast of Al Quwayr, south of Mosul, and the Iraqi Army was reported to be within {{convert|6|km|mi}} of the outskirts of Mosul city.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Damon |first1=Arwa |last2=Walsh |first2=Nick Paton |last3=Hume |first3=Tim |last4=McKirdy |first4=Euan |title=Iraqi forces closing in on Mosul for key ISIS battle |url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/19/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=CNN |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019092506/http://www.cnn.com/2016/10/19/middleeast/mosul-isis-operation-iraq/index.html |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The village of Kani Harami was captured after heavy fighting in the morning with the militants retreating to Abbasiyah.<ref name=\"rudaw1019\">{{cite news |title=LIVE Updates Mosul Battle: Day 3 |url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/19102016 |accessdate=19 October 2016 |publisher=[[Rudaw Media Network]] |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019215412/http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iraq/19102016 |archivedate=19 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> A total of 22 towns were reported to have been captured, with 12 by the Peshmerga and 10 by the ISF.<ref>{{cite news |title=VIDEO. Irak : avec les combattants kurdes sur la route de Mossoul |url=http://www.leparisien.fr/politique/sur-la-route-de-mossoul-19-10-2016-6225651.php |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Le Parisien |date=19 October 2016}}</ref> Nofal Hammadi, governor of the [[Nineveh Governorate]], declared that 40% of the province had been retaken from ISIL.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0645\u062d\u0627\u0641\u0638 \u0646\u064a\u0646\u0648\u0649 \u064a\u0639\u0644\u0646 \u062a\u062d\u0631\u064a\u0631 40% \u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062d\u0627\u0641\u0638\u0629 (Nineveh Governor Announces Liberation of 40% of the Province) |url=http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/183211/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-40-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8%D8%A9/ |accessdate=19 October 2016 |work=Al Sumaria |date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161020035714/http://www.alsumaria.tv/news/183211/%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8-%D9%86%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%88%D9%89-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B1-40-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%B8%D8%A9/ |archivedate=20 October 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe offensive to retake the town of [[Bashiqa]] northeast of Mosul was delayed due to lack of logistical support.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u